        "## Light: without LEDs, the tunnel stays invisible",
        "The underground lives on lighting - literally, because without light there is simply nothing to see. Warm white LEDs on the platforms create that typical station atmosphere; cool white spots in the tunnel tube add technical accents. The wiring disappears elegantly into the plinth: between the MILS levels there is plenty of room for cables and distributors. If you like, add illuminated destination boards made from printed tiles - small details with a big effect in the half-dark.",
        "## The open flank: show what you built",
